data.meta_description: A Protestant nation refers to a country where the dominant form of Christianity is Protestantism, a branch of Christianity that emerged during the Reformation in the 16th century.
data.text:
Definition

A Protestant nation refers to a country where the dominant form of Christianity is Protestantism, a branch of Christianity that emerged during the Reformation in the 16th century.
